{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/manifests/jack-v-at-ultimatum-festival-1985-05-01.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"en":["Jack V at Ultimatum Festival 1985-05-01 "]},"homepage":[{"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985","type":"Text","label":{"en":["Jack V at Ultimatum Festival 1985-05-01 "]},"format":"text/html"}],"metadata":[{"label":{"en":["Description"]},"value":{"en":["The following is a transcription of Jack V performance of \"Poesie Guerriere\" at Ultimatum, Wednesday, May 1st, 1985 at the Foufounes Electriques. Alan Lord provides a description and interpretation of the performance in his memoirs: \n\"For his performance—called Poesie guerriere—Jack read a few texts, then smashed a mirror, invoking \"seven years of bad luck!\" He then stripped down to the waist and smeared war paint on his face. He started dancing, prancing and swaying in abandon like a wild man, and soon a regiment of a dozen drummers joined him onstage one by one—a post-punk marching band—martially rat-tatting their snares. Jack was feline and menacing, irresistibly magnetic. This was poetry beyond words, like Alex nodding you his glass of Moloko Plus in A Clockwork Orange. When we watch Jack's clip we feel the shock of realizing his performance anticipates by some 35 years that of Joaquin Phoenix dancing down the stairs in Joker.\" Jack V entered the alternative scene by playing bass for Roro d’Haiti and later for Monty Casin, in First Aid Brigade. Lord determines that ultimately, Jack V \"gave the most memorable performance of the festival\". "]}},{"label":{"en":["Language"]},"value":{"en":["English"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/jack_v_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01/canvas/16","type":"Canvas","duration":1221,"annotations":[{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/manifests/jack_v_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01-canvas16-1","type":"AnnotationPage","label":{"en":["Default"]},"items":[{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/jack_v_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01/canvas/16/page1","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Light static.","format":"text/plain","motivation":"commenting"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Recording","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"}],"target":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/jack_v_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01/canvas/16#t=0,5"},{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/jack_v_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01/canvas/16/page1","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Buzzing.","format":"text/plain","motivation":"commenting"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Recording","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"}],"target":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/jack_v_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01/canvas/16#t=5,6"},{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/jack_v_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01/canvas/16/page1","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Performs \"Poesie Guerriere\", vocalizes, sings and recites text [French] [underscored by recorded buzzing sound].","format":"text/plain","motivation":"commenting"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Jack V","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"}],"target":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/jack_v_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01/canvas/16#t=6,59"},{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/jack_v_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01/canvas/16/page1","body":[